Recently

There's a video circulating on the Internet

It's a hot topic on the Internet

According to the website, the woman, who is an Australian Chinese, did not wear a mask when she returned to Beijing. Facing the community epidemic prevention staff to persuade, the woman not only did not listen to advice, but also shouted "life-saving harassment. ". Subsequently, the police arrived and issued a warning to him that he must be quarantined in his home for 14 days according to regulations.

Later, some netizens pointed out that the woman was an employee of Bayer.

On the evening of March 17, Bayer said on its official Weibo Account that Bayer has always abided by the laws and regulations of the country where it operates and firmly supported the Chinese government and people in their fight against the epidemic. Bayer was the first to verify the videos circulating on the Internet. The person in question was found to be an employee of Bayer. In response to the incident, Bayer announced that the employee will be terminated, effective immediately.

The women in the containment area asked for mineral water

According to the Beijing Daily, a video of a woman insisting on drinking mineral water at a central quarantine point attracted public attention yesterday. According to netizens, the woman in the video is a returned student from Italy. During her isolation in Pudong, Shanghai, she was dissatisfied with the boiled water provided and insisted on drinking mineral water.

According to the video posted on Weibo@china, a woman in the quarantine area had a dispute with staff over water and tried to rush out of the area before police arrived to settle the dispute.

In the video, a man dressed in a protective suit with the words "special police" is asking a young woman: "just whether to break out of the card? " The woman denied this.

"This is not a hotel, this is a quarantine area... " the police officer then verbally warned the woman. But before she could finish her sentence, she said, "the quarantine area also needs to protect human rights. I haven't had water for three days. "

Originally, the woman said to drink mineral water, but also to express mail to the quarantine zone, thus with the staff dispute. Staff said that the quarantine area has boiling kettle, everyone is boiled water to drink. But the woman said boiled water is full of impurities, there is no way to drink.

In the video, the police respond to the woman said: "Here is not for you to travel. "

According to China economic weekly, a video shot by a Chinese returnee has been the subject of heated debate. The footage showed a man returning from Italy who was dissatisfied with the poor conditions in the airport's waiting area and the length of the wait, saying, "look, everyone, we are back from Europe, the treatment is like this, let you stay the night. ".

The recent increase in the number of returned Chinese, the airport quarantine inspection and evacuation of passengers increased pressure. It is reported that the man's flight arrived at the airport in the late evening of the 11th, because of more people waiting for quarantine inspection, the airport has been divided into designated areas to arrange the return of Chinese.

According to a woman at the scene, due to the large number of passengers arriving that night, for a time out of control, passengers need to take the airport bus, but the car carrying capacity is limited, resulting in airport passengers stranded.

Shaq Island has commented:

There have been a number of recent incidents of people returning from overseas making angry comments at the quarantine points: some people with cough symptoms do not cooperate with the entry quarantine procedures, some people in the quarantine points do not drink non-mineral water temper.

Island uncle felt that in the current critical moment to prevent the importation of foreign epidemic, strengthen entry quarantine is the most important control, quarantine is every entry personnel should comply with the obligations.

The lesson is profound enough that Guo, a Zhengzhou resident, came home with a virus that he did not tell the world about; that the United States came to Beijing to confirm a case and lied about the symptoms to a flight attendant, causing great public anger!

Recently, the domestic epidemic situation is good, some people choose to return to the country, there are media reports that the British direct flight tickets up to 180,000 A ticket. Immigration control is a tough job.

The island uncle wants to say, the medical care, the security personnel bears the more heavy work pressure, more one understands, more some forbearance, passes this step together. We don't expect you to say thank you, but don't make trouble.

Do International students want to go back to China? Zhang Wenhong said

Although there are all the above-mentioned non-cooperation with the epidemic prevention work of entry personnel, but can not deny that most of the entry personnel or actively cooperate with the relevant departments of epidemic prevention.

The plane carrying Italian student Yao Yao (not his real name) landed in Shenzhen on the afternoon of March 10, according to the Shenzhen Special Zone newspaper. She had been in self-imposed isolation in Italy for 20 days. She has been on the road for nearly 30 hours since she boarded a plane at 6 am on the 9th, nearly three times the usual time. All the way to eat and drink water, do not dare to take off the mask, until they were sent to the isolation point to relax. Before returning, Yao Yao had declared all the ways it could do so, and the first thing it did when it got off the plane was to report to the airport staff. Yao Yao is under quarantine at the hotel. NUCLEIC ACID test is negative. On the night of the return flight, the Italians declared "vassal state" .

According to the China Youth Daily, in order to assist overseas Chinese and overseas Chinese to do a good job in the prevention and control of the new crown pneumonia, on the afternoon of March 16(China Standard Time) , shanghai medical experts, including Zhang Wenhong, director of Infection Department of Mount Hua Hospital affiliated to Fudan University, will join overseas Chinese community representatives from Italy, France, Malaysia, Australia and the United Arab Emirates to share their experience in the prevention, control and treatment of NCP, the positive suggestions were given to the prevention and control of overseas epidemic situation.

On the question of whether international students should return to their home countries, zhang Wenhong said: "whether back or not, you have to consider two issues, the first epidemic to how long? "? Did you come back and decide never to go back? What if the epidemic goes on for six months, and you don't even have a job to study? And second, what if you don't come back and stay there?"

Zhang Wenhong suggested that effective personal protection could prevent the disease. Keep your social distance, wash your hands frequently, and wear a mask, all three. "So far, I haven't seen anyone who does these three things particularly well and is infected. It's very unlikely. "

Zhang Wenhong believes that doing a good job of personal protection, so that they do not get sick is the best way

How do you convict someone who refuses to be quarantined and deliberately conceals?

In February this year, the Supreme Court, the Supreme People's Procuratorate, the Ministry of Public Security, the Ministry of Justice and others issued the opinions on punishing according to law the prevention and control of the epidemic of COVID-19 pneumonia, the conviction and punishment of the above-mentioned acts are clearly stipulated: the newly diagnosed patients refuse to enter public places in isolation and are convicted and punished for endangering public security by dangerous means.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yang Wanming, vice president of the Supreme Court, said that since the outbreak of the epidemic, the overwhelming majority of the people have been able to voluntarily cooperate with and support the epidemic prevention and control measures taken by the relevant departments according to law, but some places also appear to resist the epidemic prevention and control measures.

For example, people who have been diagnosed with or suspected of COVID-19 infection refuse to comply with the quarantine treatment measures, or have been in and out of the affected areas, have developed symptoms of infection such as fever, and still deliberately conceal or even enter public places.

"The above-mentioned acts not only endanger the life and health of the perpetrators themselves, but also endanger public health and public safety and should be punished according to law. In order to accurately apply the law, the opinion makes a clear distinction between the different circumstances of the case and, in particular, the subjective attitude of the perpetrator, with regard to conviction and punishment,"he said.

One is the crime of endangering public security by dangerous means. According to the law on the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases, patients who have been diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia, pathogen carriers and suspected patients should be treated in isolation. Those who have been diagnosed or are suspected of violating their legal obligations by refusing isolation treatment and entering public places are clearly "knowingly committing an offence" , are desirous of or allow the spread of COVID-19 to endanger public safety, and in this regard, according to law, the crime of endangering public security by dangerous means should be punished.

In view of this, the opinion makes it clear that any person who intentionally spreads COVID-19 to infect pneumonia pathogens and endangers public security shall, in accordance with the provisions of articles one hundred and fourteen and one hundred and fifteen of the criminal law, conviction and punishment of the crime of endangering public security by dangerous means: first, the already diagnosed COVID-19 pneumonia patient, the pathogen carrier, refuses the isolation treatment, or breaks the isolation treatment without expiration of the isolation period, and enter a public place or public transport; Second, a suspected COVID-19 pneumonia patient refuses to undergo isolation treatment or leaves isolation treatment before the period of isolation has expired, and enters a public place or public transport, to spread the COVID-19.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In addition, they can also be convicted of obstructing the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases. With the approval of the State Council, the COVID-19 has decided to adopt measures for the prevention and control of Class A infectious diseases in cases of pneumonia.

The opinions clearly state that other violations of the provisions of the Law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases have refused to implement the prevention and control measures provided by the health and epidemic prevention institutions according to law, thus causing the spread of COVID-19 or posing a serious risk of transmission, should be in accordance with the provisions of Article Three hundred and thirty of the criminal law, to hinder the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases conviction and punishment.
